{"link":"servo.org","html":"<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n  <title>Servo, the parallel browser engine</title>\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"css/bootstrap.css\">\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"css/style.css\">\n</head>\n\n<body>\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n        <h1 id=\"page-title\" class=\"page-header\">\n          Servo, the Parallel Browser Engine Project\n        </h1>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n        <h3 class=\"description\">\n          <b>Servo</b> is a modern, high-performance\n          browser engine designed for both application and embedded use.\n        </h3>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <br>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"col-sm-12 col-lg-6\">\n        <p class=\"info\">\n          Sponsored by Mozilla and written in the new systems\n          programming language <a href=\"https://www.rust-lang.org\">Rust</a>,\n          the Servo project aims to achieve better parallelism,\n          security, modularity, and performance.\n        </p>\n        <a class=\"btn btn-lg btn-primary center-block\" href=\"https://download.servo.org\">Download Servo nightly build</a><br><br>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"col-sm-12 col-lg-6\">\n        <div class=\"thumbnail text-center\">\n          <a href=\"screenshot.png\">\n            <img class=\"media-object\" src=\"screenshot.png\" alt=\"servo.org rendered with Servo\">\n          </a>\n          This page rendered with Servo on 3 July 2016\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n        <div id=\"community\">\n\n          <p>\n            Created by Mozilla Research, the Servo project is being built by a global\n            community, from individual contributors to companies such as Mozilla and\n            Samsung.\n          </p>\n\n          <p>\n            Servo currently supports Linux, macOS, Windows, and Android.\n          </p>\n\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n        <h2 class=\"header\">Getting Started</h2>\n        <h3>Prerequisites</h3>\n        <p>\n          You can find what you need to install on your particular system\n          <a href=\"https://github.com/servo/servo#setting-up-your-environment\"> on our GitHub page</a>.\n        </p>\n\n        <h3>Building</h3>\n        <p>\n          Servo is built with Cargo, the Rust package manager. We also use Mozilla's\n          Mach tools to orchestrate the build and other tasks.\n        </p>\n\n        <h4>Normal build</h4>\n        <p>\n          To build Servo in development mode. This is useful for development, but the\n          resulting binary is very slow.\n        </p>\n\n        <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/servo/servo\ncd servo\n./mach build --dev\n./mach run tests/html/about-mozilla.html</code></pre>\n\n        <p>\n          For benchmarking, performance testing, or real-world use, add the\n          <code>--release</code> flag to create an optimized build:\n        </p>\n\n        <pre><code>./mach build --release\n./mach run --release tests/html/about-mozilla.html</code></pre>\n\n        <h3>Running</h3>\n        <p>\n          Use <code>./mach run [url]</code> to run Servo.\n        </p>\n\n        <h4>Commandline Arguments</h4>\n\n        <ul>\n          <li>\n            <code>-p INTERVAL</code> turns on the profiler and dumps\n            info to the console every INTERVAL seconds\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            <code>-s SIZE</code> sets the tile size for painting;\n            defaults to 512\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            <code>-z</code> disables all graphical output; useful for\n            running JS / layout tests\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n        <h2 class=\"header\">Contributing</h2>\n\n        <p id=\"contributing\">\n          The Servo Project encourages contributions from\n          experienced and new developers alike.\n\n          Look at the links at the bottom of the page to learn more and join\n          hundreds of contributors worldwide working to help make Servo even better.\n        </p>\n\n        <p>\n          Contributions to Servo or its dependencies should be made in the form of\n          GitHub pull requests. Each pull request will be reviewed by a core contributor\n          (someone with permission to land patches) and either landed in the main tree\n          or given feedback for changes that would be required. All contributions should\n          follow this format, even those from core contributors.\n        </p>\n\n        <p>\n          Should you wish to work on an issue, please claim it first by commenting on\n          the GitHub issue that you want to work on it. This is to prevent duplicated\n          efforts from contributors on the same issue.\n        </p>\n\n        <p>\n          If you're looking for easy bugs, have a look at the <a href=\"https://github.com/servo/servo/labels/E-easy\">E-Easy issue tag</a> on\n          GitHub.\n        </p>\n\n        <p>\n          See\n          <a href=\"https://github.com/servo/servo/blob/master/docs/HACKING_QUICKSTART.md\">HACKING_QUICKSTART.md</a>\n          for more information on how to start working on Servo.\n        </p>\n\n        <h3>Pull Request Checklist</h3>\n\n        <ul>\n          <li>\n            Branch from the master branch and, if needed, rebase to the current master\n            branch before submitting your pull request. If it doesn't merge cleanly with\n            master you may be asked to rebase your changes.\n          </li>\n\n          <li>\n            Don't put submodule updates in your pull request unless they are to landed\n            commits.\n          </li>\n\n          <li>\n            If your patch is not getting reviewed or you need a specific person to\n            review it, you can @-reply a reviewer asking for a review in the pull request\n            or a comment, or you can ask for a review in #servo on irc.mozilla.org.\n          </li>\n\n          <li>\n            Add tests relevant to the fixed bug or new feature. For a DOM change this\n            will usually be a web platform test; for layout, a reftest. See our\n            <a href=\"https://github.com/servo/servo/wiki/Testing\"> testing guide </a>\n            for more information.\n          </li>\n\n          <li>\n            For specific git instructions, see <a href=\"https://github.com/servo/servo/wiki/Github-workflow\">GitHub workflow\n            101.</a>\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <a class=\"btn btn-primary btn-large\" role=\"button\" href=\"https://starters.servo.org/\">Start Contributing</a>\n\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n        <h2 class=\"header\">Communication</h2>\n\n        <p>\n          Servo contributors frequent the #servo channel on\n          <a href=\"https://wiki.mozilla.org/IRC\">irc.mozilla.org.</a>\n          You can also join the\n          <a href=\"https://lists.mozilla.org/listinfo/dev-servo\">dev-servo mailing list.</a>\n        </p>\n\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n        <h2 class=\"header\">Conduct</h2>\n\n        <p>\n          We follow the\n          <a href=\"https://www.rust-lang.org/conduct.html\">Rust Code of Conduct.</a>\n        </p>\n\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\" id=\"languages\">\n      <div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n\n        <p>Our site in other languages:\n          <a href=\"/zh-CN/index.html\">简体中文</a>\n        </p>\n\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <footer>\n      <div class=\"row text-center\">\n        <div class=\"col-md-3\">\n          <a href=\"https://www.github.com/servo\">Contribute</a>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"col-md-3\">\n          <a href=\"https://github.com/servo/servo/wiki/Roadmap\">Follow Servo's Roadmap</a>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"col-md-3\">\n          <a href=\"https://blog.servo.org/\">Read the Servo blog</a>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"col-md-3\">\n          <p class=\"text-muted\">#servo on irc.mozilla.org</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </footer>\n  </div>\n\n\n\n</body>"}
